---
import BaseLayout from '@/components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import VerdictCardMock from '@/components/diagrams/VerdictCardMock.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Approach — How Moe Qadan designs and builds"
  description="The methodology. AI as production infrastructure, not a feature. Prompt engineering as system, not chat. Claude, Cursor, and Claude Design selected by task. The codebase is the source of truth."
  keywords={[
    'Moe Qadan',
    'design approach',
    'design engineering',
    'AI-assisted design',
    'prompt engineering',
    'design systems',
    'product design process',
    'Claude Design',
    'Figma',
    'Cursor',
  ]}
>
  <div class="apr">
    <div class="apr__hero">
      <div class="container-site">
        <span class="apr__eyebrow">Approach</span>
        <h1 class="apr__title">
          The model is one stage.<br />The <em>system</em> is the product.
        </h1>
        <p class="apr__subtitle">
          Most of my work isn't building from scratch. It's stepping
          into what already exists and making it better. AI runs
          through it as production infrastructure, not a feature you
          flip on.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container-site apr__body">
      <section class="apr__section" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="apr__h2">Three principles</h2>
        <ol class="apr__principles">
          <li>
            <span class="apr__principle-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="apr__principle-title">Systems before surfaces.</strong>
              <p class="apr__principle-desc">
                A page is a render of something deeper. Get the
                underlying structure right and the surface gets cheaper
                to change.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="apr__principle-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="apr__principle-title">Constraints are the brief.</strong>
              <p class="apr__principle-desc">
                Long-running stacks. Real users. Code that can't be torn
                down. Those aren't obstacles; they're the actual design
                problem.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="apr__principle-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="apr__principle-title">AI is infrastructure, not a feature.</strong>
              <p class="apr__principle-desc">
                Prompts live in the system, scoped to context, versioned,
                and budgeted. Same inputs, consistent outputs. The point
                is repeatability, not novelty.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <hr class="apr__rule" />

      <section class="apr__section" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="apr__h2">AI as production infrastructure</h2>
        <p class="apr__para">
          ChatOBD2 is the clearest example. Six deterministic reasoning
          layers run before every model call. The system prompt is
          composed per scan from a 38,000-token budget — P0 sections
          always make the cut; lower-priority sections only land if
          budget remains. Prompts are keyed by verdict tier and code
          context, not scattered across components.
        </p>
        <p class="apr__para">
          The model gets a structured spec, not a chat. That's what
          makes the output repeatable, the analytics coherent, and the
          system inspectable. A human owns every decision that ships.
        </p>

        <div class="apr__art" data-reveal>
          <span class="apr__art-caption">From inputs to verdict — ChatOBD2 product surface</span>
          <VerdictCardMock />
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="apr__rule" />

      <section class="apr__section" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="apr__h2">Tools, picked by task</h2>
        <p class="apr__para">
          Most of the work happens in code, against the components and
          tokens the product is built from. The tool is selected by what
          the task actually needs:
        </p>

        <ul class="apr__tools">
          <li>
            <span class="apr__tool-name">Claude</span>
            <span class="apr__tool-role">Reasoning, code generation, refactoring across a codebase. Default for non-trivial work.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="apr__tool-name">Cursor</span>
            <span class="apr__tool-role">Local iteration in the editor. Same code work, different interaction style.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="apr__tool-name">Figma</span>
            <span class="apr__tool-role">Precision work, design-system maintenance, handoff fidelity.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="apr__tool-name">Claude Design</span>
            <span class="apr__tool-role">Visual exploration when reasoning is faster in a frame than in code. Output lands back in the codebase.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="apr__para apr__para--note">
          The codebase is the source of truth across all of them. Tools
          are interchangeable; the system isn't.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="apr__rule" />

      <section class="apr__section" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="apr__h2">Across the work</h2>
        <p class="apr__para">
          Different products, different surfaces, different tools — but
          the same loop: understand the constraint, structure the
          intent, ship into a real system, hold the result to a
          product-quality bar.
        </p>

        <div class="apr__work-grid">
          <figure class="apr__work-shot">
            <img
              src="/images/chatobd2/hero.webp"
              alt="ChatOBD2 marketing hero with phone mockup of a live diagnostic chat."
              width="1440"
              height="900"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>
              <strong>ChatOBD2</strong> — AI-native diagnostics, designed and engineered solo.
              <a href="/work/chatobd2">Read the case study →</a>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="apr__work-shot">
            <img
              src="/images/magtek/homepage.webp"
              alt="MagTek homepage with metric story and team photography."
              width="1440"
              height="900"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>
              <strong>MagTek</strong> — UX systems and frontend across an enterprise platform.
              <a href="/work/magtek-platform">Read the case study →</a>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="apr__work-shot">
            <img
              src="/images/sawa/hero.webp"
              alt="Sawa marketing hero — 'idk, you pick' with phone mockup of a matched restaurant card."
              width="1440"
              height="900"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>
              <strong>Sawa</strong> — marketing site for an iMessage-native group dining app.
              <a href="/work/sawa">Read the case study →</a>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure class="apr__work-shot">
            <img
              src="/images/financial-platforms/chase.webp"
              alt="Chase homepage built on the InvestCloud framework."
              width="1440"
              height="900"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption>
              <strong>Advisor platforms</strong> — multi-tenant frontend across major institutions.
              <a href="/work/financial-platforms">Read the case study →</a>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .apr__hero {
    padding-top: calc(60px + var(--space-10));
    padding-bottom: var(--space-10);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .apr__hero {
      padding-top: calc(64px + var(--space-16));
      padding-bottom: var(--space-12);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    }
  }

  .apr__eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .apr__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(36px, 8vw, 72px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .apr__title em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .apr__subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(16px, 1.7vw, 19px);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .apr__body {
    padding-bottom: var(--space-16);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-12);
    max-width: 1080px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .apr__body {
      padding-bottom: var(--space-24);
      gap: var(--space-16);
    }
  }

  .apr__rule {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .apr__section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }

  .apr__h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(24px, 3vw, 36px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .apr__para {
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }

  .apr__para--note {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
  }

  .apr__principles {
    counter-reset: apr-principles;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }

  .apr__principles li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 36px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    align-items: baseline;
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .apr__principles li {
      padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-7);
    }
  }

  .apr__principle-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    padding-top: 2px;
  }

  .apr__principle-title {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(18px, 2vw, 22px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .apr__principle-desc {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(14px, 1.4vw, 16px);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .apr__art {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .apr__art-caption {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
  }

  .apr__art :global(.verdict-mock__head) {
    display: none;
  }

  .apr__art :global(.verdict-mock) {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .apr__tools {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .apr__tools {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-4);
    }
  }

  .apr__tools li {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);
  }

  .apr__tool-name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-text);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .apr__tool-role {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .apr__work-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .apr__work-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-6);
    }
  }

  .apr__work-shot {
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .apr__work-shot img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }

  .apr__work-shot figcaption {
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2px;
  }

  .apr__work-shot figcaption strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .apr__work-shot figcaption a {
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-border);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    font-size: 12px;
    transition: color 150ms, text-decoration-color 150ms;
  }

  .apr__work-shot figcaption a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-accent);
  }
</style>
